{"editorCode":"  \n\t\t;The safe\n\n;Clara found a safe and she tries to unlock it. If she finds the right combination of a and b, a wire closes into a rectangle and the safe is then unlocked. She found it quite easy and then she decided to change the combination in order to make it unlock less easily.\n;Thus she enters an adventure of solving a linear system. Can you help her?\n\n;For further instructions click on the papyrus button.\n\n\nclean\ncombination 2 5\n\nTO combination :a :b\npu setpos [0 -100 0] pd\nfd 80 rt 90 fd 120 rt 90\nfd 10*:a+20*:b rt 90 fd 15*:a+30*:b\nrt 90\npu lt 90 fd 100 pd rt 90\nend\n\n\nTO combination2 :a :b\nsetpos [0 -100 0]  ; moves the avatar\nfd ...\nrt 90 \nfd ...\nrt 90\nfd ... \nrt 90 \nfd ...\nrt 90\npu lt 90 fd 100 pd rt 90 ;moves the avatar\nend\n\nclean\ncombination2 2 5\n","hiddenCode":[],"sceneCode":"","cameraPos":{"x":0,"y":1.2246467991473532e-14,"z":200},"character":"Bird","notes":"                         ..........................................\n                                       The safe\n                         ..........................................\n\nINTRODUCTION:\nRun the command \"combination 2 5\".  A broken line with two vertical and two horizontal parts is constructed.\n\nTASK 1:\nActivate the variation tool (by clicking on the avatar's light blue trace) and set the value range of the variables a and b from 0 to 12 with step value 0.1.\n\nZero the values of the variables a and b and then change each one of them separately in order to understand the way they affect the length of each part of the broken line.\n\nTry to \"close\" the broken line in order to form a rectangle and write down the values of a and b for which the rectangle is formed.\n\na= ...      b= ...       \n\nDoes the broken lines close for more than that one combination?\n\nTry when a = 4    b=?          \n     when a = 2    b=?                 \n     when a = 5    b=?\n\nTASK 2:\nStudy the procedure \"combination\" that constructed the